<subSubSection pageId="147" pageNumber="908" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="147.[184,1395,1748,3282]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,417,2893,2926]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Rufous Tube-nosed Bats roost in caves, trees, and houses. They are known to hibernate in cave crevices during winter, near 
<collectingRegion box="[939,1037,2932,2965]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">Beijing</collectingRegion>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1165,2932,2965]" name="China" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">China</collectingCountry>
,calls are a steep FM sweep with an average start frequency of 104-1 kHz, end frequency 34-9 kHz, peak frequency 88-8 kHz, duration 4-1 milliseconds, and interpulse interval 63-9 milliseconds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
